<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
This variety differ from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton manampetsae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manampetsae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Croton manampetsae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that the leaves are mostly alternate (vs. opposite) and in the lepidote indumentum on the abaxial side of the leaves (vs. stellate trichomes). It will likely be described as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
